1.  Server is the metal box.
2.  Domain name is the beautiful textual representation for the IP Address
3.  ...Canonical Name? Yes, it is CNAME!
    According to google:
    www is a CNAME (Canonical Name) DNS record-type in www.foobar.com since it also points to the same IP address as foobar.com and if the IP address changes we can only record changes in the DNS A record of foobar.com
4.  The web server is the software that handles external requests
5.  Application servers will format and return the responses to web server requests
    Google says:
    The function of the application server is to act as host (or container) for the user's business logic while facilitating access to and performance of the business application.
6.  Database is the storage for data ordered in a relational manner.
7.  ...HTTP?

SPOF:   Single Point of Failure